Description: VG condition Paul Reed Smith Korina McCarty with Soapbar pickups. *** re-listing this due to an issue with the prior auction; there was some finish damage that I didn't look at well enough before I corrected the listing (causing it to be locked), so the last auction was cancelled so the item could be re-listed. Damage is identified in picture the last picture *** Wide fat neck profile. Not sure what year it is, but I’d bet against it having a Brazilian rosewood fingerboard. There are two marks on the upper edge of the body where the arm cut would be, which are shown in detail in picture 12. Both marks are through the finish; the rearward one is larger at about .26", the forward one is about .22". These are both very minor marks (I didn't notice them when I originally photographed the guitar), but they are there and they are through the finish. There are some minor scratches in the back and a pencil lead sized dink in the finish, but no buckle rash. I can’t see or feel any blemishes on the neck surface, nor can I see any swirling on the front of the body – but it’s very hard to tell from this finish (see pictures). The headstock is pretty dusty, but I haven’t played it since I changed the strings… so I didn’t feel like cutting off the basically new strings to clean the headstock. Since I bought this several years ago, it’s been mostly on display with the rest of my guitars… very little play time, maybe a couple of hours. Auction does include what appears to be an original PRS case (it's not marked as such on the outside, but the fit is formed). I don’t know how it was handled prior to my getting it, but I’ve tried to include pictures of the frets, and I don’t see any significant fretwear, particularly around the G string 3-5 where it tends to show up first. It’s a great guitar and I hope the next guy plays the hell out of it. Shipping will be $75 insured by UPS to the continental U.S. ONLY - I'm not going to ship this internationally. Please ask any questions you have before bidding, refrain from bidding if you don’t intend to pay, and good luck!
Title: Paul Reed Smith McCarty Korina Soap-bar (PRS)
ConditionDescription: VG condition.  Case has some scratches and scuffs.
